Field Detail

DEVICE_ORIENTATION_ANGLE

public static final com.greystripe.sdk.UniqueIntegerMap DEVICE_ORIENTATION_ANGLE
This is the device orientation angle from its natural orientation. For example, Galaxy S4 natural orientation is portrait

--------- right down = 90 degree | x| -> --------------- | | | | | | | x| | | |------------ | ---------

--------- left down = 270 degree | x| -> --------------- | | |x | | | | | | | |------------ | ---------

-> no rotation = 0 degree --------- --------- | x| | x| | | | | | | | | | | | | --------- --------- -> up side down = 180 degree --------- --------- | x| | | | | | | | | | | | | | x| --------- ---------
